body:
This issue is at the root of the second problem reported in https://github.com/verilator/verilator/issues/3576.

It's easiest to explain using an example.

```systemverilog
module t(output logic clk_dly);
   logic clk = 0;

   always clk = #1ns ~clk;

   always clk_dly = #1ps clk;

   initial #100 $finish;
endmodule 
```

The first `always` flips the clock every nanosecond. Because it has a delay, the clock has the delay trigger as one of its extra domains.

The second always is sensitive to `clk`. This is a combinational dependency, so really it is transitively sensitive to the delay trigger. It also has a 1 picosecond delay inside.

This is where the problem is: because it has a delay, it also lights up the delay trigger. Which means it triggers itself... every picosecond.

So in this example, for each clock half cycle, the simulation eval loop runs a thousand times. Obviously it should only run twice per half cycle.
